e%20charges%20related%20to%20some%20historical%20customer%20returns%20that%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20resolved%20and%20some%20costs%20to%20receive%20inventory%20that%20was%20pulled%20forward%20into%20Q1%20ahead%20of%20anticipated%20tariffs%2C%26quot%3B%20Olsavsky%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20those%20charges%2C%20the%20operating%20profit%20margin%20of%20Amazon's%20North%20America%20retail%20business%20would%20have%20been%20almost%20one%20percentage%20point%20higher%2C%20the%20CFO%20said.%20That%20equates%20to%20a%20roughly%20%24800%20million%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20international%20retail%20business%2C%20it%20would%20have%20had%20an%20operating%20margin%20that%20was%20roughly%200.7%25%20higher%2C%20Olsavsky%20added.%20That%20equates%20to%20about%20%24200%20million%20in%20one-time%20charges%2C%20for%20a%20grand%20total%20of%20roughly%20%241%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20notable%20here%20is%20that%20the%20losses%20stem%20from%20two%20persistent%20concerns%20%E2%80%94%20tariffs%20and%20customer%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETariffs%20have%20created%20a%20climate%20of%20unpredictability%2C%20Amazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20said%20during%20Thursday's%20analyst%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20did%20some%20forward%20buying%20for%20its%20wholesale%20business%2C%20while%20some%20third-party%20sellers%20shipped%20inventory%20ahead%20of%20schedule%20to%20avoid%20tariff%20hikes%2C%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Amazon%20hasn't%20seen%20the%20average%20selling%20price%20on%20Amazon%20%26quot%3Bappreciably%20go%20up%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNone%20of%20us%20knows%20exactly%20where%20tariffs%20will%20settle%20or%20when%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomer%20returns%20have%20also%20become%20a%20growing%20problem%20for%20Amazon%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20company%20is%20trying%20to%20incentivize%20customers%20to%20use%20less%20costly%20return%20methods%2C%20and%20preempt%20returns%20entirely%20by%20